"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"savings","id":"idc3b88d5a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Savings Provision","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/675/s1/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–675, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-09-19"},"text":"Sept. 19, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/559"},"text":"76 Stat. 559","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/87/675/s1/e"},"text":"“Claims for benefits under [former] sections 2001 through 2009 of chapter 41 of title 38, United States Code, for any benefit week beginning before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-01-31"},"text":"January 31, 1960","children":[],"tail":", which claims are pending on the date these sections are repealed ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-09-19"},"text":"Sept. 19, 1962","children":[],"tail":"], shall be adjudicated in the same manner and with the same effect as if the sections had not been repealed. For the purpose of administering the program with respect to such claims, all functions, powers, and duties conferred upon the Secretary of Labor by sections 2001 through 2009 are continued in effect, and all rules and regulations established by the Secretary of Labor pursuant to these sections, and in effect when the sections are repealed, shall remain in full force and effect until modified or suspended.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idc3b88d5b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Employment Assistance and Services for Veterans Ineligible for Assistance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/tV/s512"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466, title V, § 512","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2207"},"text":"94 Stat. 2207","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dA/s101/f/tVIII/s405/d/28"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. A, § 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(d)(28), (f)(20)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-337"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–337","children":[],"tail":", 2681–424, 2681–432, provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/277/dA/s101/f/tVIII/s405/d/28"},"text":"“The Secretary of Labor shall assure that any veteran who is made ineligible for employment assistance under chapter 41 of title 38, United States Code, by virtue of the amendments made by section 503(1) of this Act [amending this section] shall be provided with the employment assistance and services made available under the provisions of the Act entitled ‘An Act to provide for the establishment of a national employment system and for cooperation with the States in the promotion of such system, and for other purposes’, approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1933-06-06"},"text":"June 6, 1933","children":[],"tail":" (commonly referred to as the ‘Wagner-Peyser Act’), ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s49–49k"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 49–49k","children":[],"tail":"), title I of the Workforce Investment Act of 1998 [former "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s2801"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 2801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], and other applicable provisions of law.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idc3b88d5c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"ta